			    STPJS 357</div>
  <p class="cont">vision either in this world or the world of spirits. Hence God hath made a provision that every spirit
  in the eternal world can be ferreted out and saved unless he has committed that unpardonable sin
  which cannot be remitted to him either in this world<span class="footRef">1</span> or the world of spirits.<span class="footRef">2</span> God has wrought out
  a salvation<span class="footRef">3</span> for all men,<span class="footRef">4</span> unless they have committed a certain sin; and every man who has a friend
  in the eternal world can save him, unless he has committed the unpardonable sin.<span class="footRef">5</span> And so you can
  see how far you can be a savior.<span class="footRef">6</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The Unpardonable Sin</div>
  <p class="std">A man cannot commit the unpardonable sin<span class="footRef">7</span> after the dissolution of the body, and there is a way
  possible for escape. Knowledge saves<span class="footRef">8</span> a man; and in the world of spirits<span class="footRef">9</span> no man can be exalted<span class="footRef">10</span>
  but by knowledge. So long as a man will not give heed to the commandments,<span class="footRef">11</span> he must abide
  without salvation. If a man has knowledge, he can be saved;<span class="footRef">12</span> although, if he has been guilty of great
  sins, he will be punished for them.<span class="footRef">13</span> But when he consents to obey the Gospel, whether here or in
  the world of spirits, he is saved.<span class="footRef">14</span></p>
  <p class="std">A man is his own tormenter<span class="footRef">15</span> and his own condemner.<span class="footRef">16</span> Hence the saying, They shall go into
  the lake that burns with fire and brimstone.<span class="footRef">17</span> The torment of disappointment<span class="footRef">18</span> in the mind of man
  is as exquisite<span class="footRef">19</span> as a lake burning with fire and brimstone.<span class="footRef">20</span> I say, so is the torment of man.</p>
  <p class="std">I know the Scriptures<span class="footRef">21</span> and understand them. I said, no man can commit the unpardonable sin<span class="footRef">22</span>
  after the dissolution of the body, nor in this life, until he receives the Holy Ghost;<span class="footRef">23</span> but they must
  do it in this world. Hence the salvation of Jesus Christ was wrought out for all men,<span class="footRef">24</span> in order to
  triumph over the devil;<span class="footRef">25</span> for if it did not catch him in one place, it would in another; for he stood up
  as a Savior.<span class="footRef">26</span> All will suffer<span class="footRef">27</span> until they obey Christ himself.<span class="footRef">28</span></p>
  <p class="std">The contention in heaven was&mdash;Jesus said there would be certain souls that would not be
  saved;<span class="footRef">29</span> and the devil said he could save them all,<span class="footRef">30</span> and laid his plans before the grand council,<span class="footRef">31</span>
  who gave their vote in favor of Jesus Christ.<span class="footRef">32</span> So the devil rose up in rebellion against God,<span class="footRef">33</span> and
  was cast down,<span class="footRef">34</span> with all who put up their heads for him.<span class="footRef">35</span> (Book of Moses&mdash;Pearl of Great Price,
  Chap. 4:1–4;<span class="footRef">36</span> Book of Abraham, Chap. 3:23–28.)<span class="footRef">37</span></p>
